**Girão-Hunter (2024):**

f(n) ≤ C · 2^n / n^{1-o(1)}

This gives an exponential upper bound — some odd cycle of length O(2^n/n) must appear.

**Janzer-Yip (2025):**

f(n) ≤ C · n^{3/2} · 2^{n/2}

This is the current best upper bound! The 2^{n/2} factor is much smaller than the previous 2^n.

**Erdős Problem #609: OPEN**

Estimate f(n), the minimum odd cycle length forced in n-colorings of K_{2^n+1}.

Best bounds:
- Lower: 2^{c√(log n)}
- Upper: n^{3/2} · 2^{n/2}

The exponential gap remains a major open problem.
